    <div xml:id="PN352">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>tēeṅkoṇṭa veṇmaṇṭaiyāṉ</l>
<l>vī<gap quantity="18" reason="lost" unit="character"/>kaṟakkun</l>
<l>tavalvakutta pacuṅkuṭaiyāṟ</l>
<l>putaṉmullaip pūppaṟikkun</l>
<l>tāmpal vaḷḷit toṭikkai makaḷir</l>
<l>kuṉṟēṟip puṉaṟpāyiṟ</l>
<l>puṟavāyāṟ puṉalvaḷa<gap quantity="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="12" reason="lost" unit="character"/>noṭainaṟaviṉ</l>
<l>māvaṇ ṭittaṉ veṇṇel vēli</l>
<l>yuṟantai yaṉṉa vuraicā ṉaṉkalaṅ</l>
<l>koṭuppavuṅ koḷāa ṉe<gap quantity="12" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/>rtanta nākiḷa vēṅkaiyiṟ</l>
<l>katirttoḷi tikaḻu  nuṇpal cuṇaṅkiṉ</l>
<l>mākkaṇ malarnta mulaiya ṭaṉṉaiyuñ</l>
<l>ciṟukō luḷaiyum puravi <g rend="vowel-sign">e</g><gap quantity="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="18" reason="lost" unit="character"/>yamarē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even if he(?) were to give</l>
<l>good ornaments/vessels worthy to be spoken about, like the Uṟantai</l>
<l>with a fence of white paddy of great generous Tittaṉ,</l>
<l>with toddy to barter……………….</l>
<l>…………………………………</l>
<l>…………………………..</l>
<l>women with hands [wearing] lotus stalk bangles leaping into the flood,</l>
<l>where they pull out the flowers of jasmine from bushes</l>
<l>into green baskets divided into compartments(?),</l>
<l>where they hide…………………..</l>
<l>in white bowls that hold honey,</l>
<l>	he would not take [them].</l>
<l>To her with breasts blooming with dark nipples, </l>
<l>with many fine beauty spots that shine [and] glitter in the light</l>
<l>like youthful young kino [blossoms] given……..</l>
<l>…………………………………</l>
<l>…………………………………..</l>
<l>horse ??? ……….</l>
<l>……………………….fight.</l>
</lg>
